jobs.description:
Our partner is the world leader in specialty glass and ceramics. They create and make keystone components that enable high-technology systems for consumer electronics, mobile, emissions control, telecommunications, and life sciences.  
 Join their dynamic EMEA team as a CSS Associate and take ownership of high-impact data validation and invoice management processes! 
   
 As a CSS Associate in the RTP Data Services team, you will be responsible for ensuring the integrity and accuracy of our financial data. You’ll act as a gatekeeper for incoming invoices, ensuring that every transaction aligns perfectly with our standards and purchase orders. 


 Invoice Validation: Manage electronic invoices, validate data, and handle supplier communications (including rejections). 


 End-to-End Processing: Verify invoice information, perform PO matching, and post approved invoices in SAP, S4Hana, or PS . 


 Quality Control: Perform daily, periodic, and yearly quality checks to maintain top-tier data standards. 


 Issue Resolution: Report problematic cases and provide professional support for customer service inquiries. 


 Elvárások / Requirements 


 College/university degree; 


 Experience in AP at a multinational company or SSC is an advantage; 


 Intermediate English knowledge; 


 Good computer literacy; 


 Service and customer orientation; 


 Good communication skills; 


 Team player; 


 Accountability and accuracy; 


 Ability to work under pressure and to meet deadlines, ability to set right priorities. 


   
 Amit nyújtunk / Benefits 

 Cafeteria  
 Yearly bonus 
 Hybrid workplace 
 Life- and accident insurance for every colleagues

